<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_æmbyjyn" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma">
        <orth>æmbyjyn</orth>
        <form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp">
            <orth>æmbyd</orth>
        </form>
    </form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal">
        <orth>æmbujun</orth>
        <form type="inflected" subtype="ptcp">
            <orth>æmbud</orth>
        </form>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>гнить</q>
        </cit>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>rot</q>
        </cit>
    </sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>særd dyn mа ʽmbyjænt, zymæg dyn ma sælænt</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>пусть у тебя летом не гниют, зимой не замерзают</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>let you not rot in the summer, not freeze in the winter</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <biblScope xml:lang="ru">из посвящения покойнику</biblScope>
                <biblScope xml:lang="en">from dedication to a dead person</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>c’yfy wærmy dæ bambyjyn kodton</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>я сгноила тебя в грязной яме</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>I rotted you in a dirty pit</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ОЭ"/>
                <biblScope>I 40</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>særd dyn mа ʽmbyjænt, zymæg dyn ma sælænt</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>пусть у тебя летом не гниют, зимой не замерзают</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>let you not rot in the summer, not freeze in the winter</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <biblScope xml:lang="ru">из посвящения покойнику</biblScope>
                <biblScope xml:lang="en">from dedication to a dead person</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>c’yfy wærmy dæ bambyjyn kodton</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>я сгноила тебя в грязной яме</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>I rotted you in a dirty pit</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ОЭ"/>
                <biblScope>I 40</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*ham-pu-</w></mentioned>,
        сращение преверба <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (← %iham-%i) с корнем %iрū-%i
        ‘гнить’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>anbūsīdan</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>pūsīdan</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>hambūsītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>pay-:
                pūd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>piy-: pud-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pū-</w><gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
                ><w>pūduk</w><gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>рīо</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><lang/><w>pītk</w><gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>pĭw-: pəd-</w><gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pū-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><w>puyeiti</w><gloss><q>гниет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><w>a-puyant</w><gloss><q>не гниющий</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>рū-</w><gloss><q>гниет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>puti</w><gloss><q>гнить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πύω</w><gloss><q>вызываю
            нагноение</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><w>πύθω</w><gloss><q>гною</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>pus</w><gloss><q>гной</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>puteo</w><gloss><q>гнию</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>putidus</w><gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>faul</w><gloss><q>гнилой</q></gloss></mentioned>. Предшествие %im%i
        предотвратило обычный для осетинского переход %ip%i → %if%i, но повлекло озвончение %ip%i →
        %ib%i. Старым каузативом от %iæmbujun%i является %iæmbawun%i q. v. Сюда же <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fawyn"/> ‘хулить’. Ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifyd%i
        ‘дурной’ считаем лексикализованным старым причастием %ipūta-%i ‘гнилой’. Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_æmbyd"/> ‘гнилой’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>II 85</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*ham-pu-</w></mentioned>,
        fusion of the preverb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (← %iham-%i) with the root
        %iрū-%i ‘rot’. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>anbūsīdan</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>pūsīdan</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>hambūsītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>pay-:
                pūd-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>piy-: pud-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pū-</w><gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
                ><w>pūduk</w><gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>рīо</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><lang/><w>pītk</w><gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>pĭw-: pəd-</w><gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pū-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w>puyeiti</w><gloss><q>it rots</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w>a-puyant</w><gloss><q>not rotting</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>рū-</w><gloss><q>it rots</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>puti</w><gloss><q>rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πύω</w><gloss><q>I cause
            suppuration</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>πύθω</w><gloss><q>I rot
                    (smth.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><lang/><w>pus</w><gloss><q>pus</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>puteo</w><gloss><q>I rot</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w>putidus</w><gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>fūls</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>faul</w><gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>. Precedence of %im%i
        prevented usual Ossetic alterntation %ip%i → %if%i, but it caused vocalisation %ip%i →
        %ib%i. An old causative to %iæmbujun%i is %iæmbawun%i q. v. Here too is <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fawyn"/> ‘blaspheme’. We consider the Ossetic <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifyd%i ‘evil’ to be an old lexalized participle %ipūta-%i
        ‘rotten’. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmbyd"/> ‘rotten’.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>II 85</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
